14/06/2007
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- US Ambassador-at-Large for War Crimes Issues Clint Williamson said on Wednesday (June 13th) that bringing war criminals to justice remains a priority for the US administration.
He was in Sarajevo for meetings with members of BiH's tripartite presidency and international representatives.
He said all agreed that bringing indictees to justice is a prerequisite for reconciliation and security in the region.
Also Wednesday, police in Republika Srpska announced that they detained three Bosnian Serbs in Novi Grad, suspected of war crimes.
Goran Petic and brothers Mladen and Zoran Djukic are accused of atrocities committed against non-Serb civilians in the area in 1992.
(Dnevni Avaz - 14/06/07;
PBS BiH, RTRS, DPA - 13/06/07)
